    "All models are trained and evaluated using 10-fold crossvalidation to ensure robustness and fair comparison.",
    "C. Evaluation MetricsFor the ANA task, we report four widely adopted metrics: F 1 M icro, F 1 M acro, accuracy, and mean Average Precision (mAP).",
    "Notably, F 1 M icro treats all instances equally, while F 1 M acro averages over all categories, allowing assessment from both global and per-class perspectives.",
    "An overall metric is also reported by averaging the above four scores.For other medical tasks, we adopt four standard metrics commonly used in MIML literature: Hamming Loss (HL), One Error (OE), Ranking Loss (RL), and Average Precision (AP), following the definitions outlined in [65].TABLE I EXPERIMENTAL RESULTS OF SOTA METHODS AND OURS ON THE TEST SET.",
